      <c01 level="series">
        <did>
          <unittitle>Military Activities</unittitle>
        </did>
        <scopecontent>
          <p>The Military Activities series covers Pepper's military career from 1908 to 1952. Pepper's MNG papers are arranged chronologically and include general administrative records as well as Pepper's accounts of his military service. There are local newspapers and investigation transcripts from the 1913 copper strike, and the 1912-14 Judge Advocate General folder also contains correspondence relating to the strike. A manuscript account of Armistice Day at the front and a journal which Pepper kept on his return trip from France describe his thoughts about the war, as well as his views on military discipline. He also kept daily diaries of his experiences during service on the Mexican border and in France.</p>
          <p>MNG files from the 1920s and 1930s contain memos and correspondence regarding plans for training camps, regulations, Camp Grayling Bulletins, and reports, essays, and speeches by Pepper. MNG records from 1935 and 1937 relate to riots in Flint and to the sit-down strike; these include essays by Pepper on military responses to civil unrest. The Veterans' Groups subseries covers fundraising, memorial events, and social activities during the 1920s and 1930s.</p>
        </scopecontent>
