      <c01 level="series">
        <did>
          <unittitle>Professional and Political Activities</unittitle>
        </did>
        <scopecontent>
          <p>The Professional and Political Activities series spans the period 1910 to 1953. Pepper's law practice, government service and Republican Party work tended to overlap, and this is evident in the correspondence files, which are arranged alphabetically. Many letters are requests for Pepper's help in obtaining jobs with the state government. Representative samples have been retained from the Attorney General's office correspondence, as have letters and legal briefs from the Michigan Life Insurance Company. The Republican Party folders includes essays, speeches and correspondence by Pepper which outline his active participation in intra-party politics and strategic planning in the 1920 and 1924 elections.</p>
        </scopecontent>
